cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new variant of the FM-index, which is a well-known compressed full-text index based on the Burrows-Wheeler transform (BWT). 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses improving the efficiency of pattern search, which is a common problem in information retrieval. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper mentions cache-friendliness, which is important in distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the worst-case number of cache misses during the search, which is related to the computational complexity of the algorithm. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possibility as the paper discusses full-text indexing, which is relevant to digital libraries.
